## 🔵 LOW Findings

### LOW-01 — `datetime.utcnow()` Deprecation (Timezone-Aware Consistency)

**Files:** [auth.py](file:///c:/Users/josma/OneDrive/Escritorio/SyqueX/backend/api/auth.py#L103,L107,L149,L162,L407), [database.py](file:///c:/Users/josma/OneDrive/Escritorio/SyqueX/backend/database.py#L40-L41)

**The Problem:**  
Mixed usage of `datetime.utcnow()` (deprecated) and `datetime.now(UTC)`. This can cause subtle timezone comparison bugs in token expiration checks.

**Fix:** Replace all `datetime.utcnow()` with `datetime.now(UTC)`.

---

### LOW-02 — Dockerfile Runs as Root

**File:** [Dockerfile](file:///c:/Users/josma/OneDrive/Escritorio/SyqueX/backend/Dockerfile)

**The Problem:**  
No `USER` directive — the container runs as root. If an attacker achieves RCE, they have full container privileges.

**Fix:**
```dockerfile
RUN adduser --disabled-password --no-create-home appuser
USER appuser
CMD ["uvicorn", "main:app", "--host", "0.0.0.0", "--port", "8000"]
```

---

### LOW-03 — `ProcessedStripeEvent` Model Has Wrong Column

**File:** [billing.py](file:///c:/Users/josma/OneDrive/Escritorio/SyqueX/backend/api/billing.py#L89)

**The Problem:**
```python
db.add(ProcessedStripeEvent(id=event.id, type=event.type))
```

But the `ProcessedStripeEvent` model in `database.py` only has `id` and `created_at` — no `type` column. This will crash on webhook processing.

---

### LOW-04 — Cron Endpoint Uses Deprecated `CRON_SECRET` Naming

**File:** [cron.py](file:///c:/Users/josma/OneDrive/Escritorio/SyqueX/backend/api/cron.py#L15)

**The Problem:**  
Uses `os.getenv("CRON_SECRET")` but `config.py` defines `INTERNAL_API_KEY`. This inconsistency means the cron secret may not be loaded from Settings validation.

**Fix:** Use `settings.INTERNAL_API_KEY` consistently.

---

### LOW-05 — Frontend Loads TailwindCSS via CDN (Client-Side)

**File:** [index.html](file:///c:/Users/josma/OneDrive/Escritorio/SyqueX/frontend/index.html#L7)

**The Problem:**
```html
<script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
```

The CDN version of Tailwind is:
- Not recommended for production (performance, caching)
- A supply-chain risk (CDN compromise = XSS on your app)
- Blocks rendering until the script loads

**Fix:** Use the Tailwind CLI, PostCSS, or Vite plugin to generate a static CSS file at build time.

